<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 7:48PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT
NORTHEASTERN ROCKINGHAM...NORTHWESTERN CASWELL...SOUTHWESTERN
PITTSYLVANIA AND SOUTHEASTERN HENRY COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF
DANVILLE...
At 748 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Axton, moving
east at 20 mph.
Winds in excess of 30 mph are possible with this storm.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Chatham...
Providence...
Mayfield...
Blairs...
and Axton.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
